            <div type="glosses">
                <note xml:id="PUBLICATIONGLOSS" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold">Publication history (<title type="book" corresp="#JRWORKSLE"><hi rend="italic">Works</hi></title> [1903])&#x2014;</hi><title type="poem" corresp="JRVILLAPLINIANA">&#x201C;Villa Pliniana&#x201D;</title> 
                    was omitted from the version of the <title type="composite" corresp="#JRACCOUNTTOUR">&#x201C;Account&#x201D;</title> in <title type="book" corresp="#JRPOEMS1891"><hi rend="italic">Poems</hi> (1891)</title>, 
                    and first published in the <title type="book" corresp="#JRWORKSLE">Library Edition</title> (<ref type="bibliography" target="bibliography.php#JRWORKSLE"><persName corresp="#JR">Ruskin</persName>, <title type="book" corresp="#JRWORKSLE"><hi rend="italic">Works</hi></title></ref>, 2:376).</p></note>
                
                <note xml:id="CLAIMEDGLOSS" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold">&#x201C;Though now those names be claimed by clay&#x201D; (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSVIII">MS VIII</title>; 
                    <title type="book" corresp="#JRWORKSLE"><hi rend="italic">Works</hi></title> [1903])&#x2014;</hi>In the <title type="book" corresp="#JRWORKSLE">Library Edition</title>, 
                    this line os altered to &#x201C;Though now their names be drowned by clay&#x201D; (<ref type="bibliography" target="bibliography.php#JRWORKSLE"><persName corresp="#JR">Ruskin</persName>, <title type="book" corresp="#JRWORKSLE"><hi rend="italic">Works</hi></title></ref>, 2:376). 
                    It is unclear whether the editors misread or attempted to improve the line, but their transcription is certainly inaccurate.</p></note>
                
                <note xml:id="PAUSEPERIOD" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold">Pause&#x2013;period (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSVIII">MS VIII</title>)&#x2014;</hi>See 
                    <ref type="note" subtype="bibliographical" target="editorial_rationale_note.php#COMMA">Editorial and Encoding Rationale and Methodology: Element, Attribute, and Value Usage&#x2014;Commas, Periods, and Other Punctuation</ref>.</p></note>
                <!--The pointer to this gloss would be <ref type="gloss_textual" target="villa_pliniana_glosses_textual.php#SPAUSEPERIOD" />.-->
